Citation.sTitle: Thermophysical and Molar Volume Aberration of Amphiphilic Eutectic Mix of Bivalent Diols and Ammonium-Ionic Liquid
Citation.sAbstract: The thermophysical delineation of four diol (Glycerol, 1, 2 Butane diol, 1, 6 Hexane diol, Ethane diol) based deep eutectic solvents (DES) were investigated in temperature range of 273 K to 323 K at atmospheric pressure. The homogenous mixture was prepared with quaternary ammonium salt and diols respectively at an identical molar ratio of 1:1 (HBA: HBD). Density and viscosity have negative response with increasing temperature. Conductivity and excess molar volume ratio increase at elevated temperature. The results obtained were correlated with linear model equations. Liquid-liquid equilibrium of ternary mixture formed with PEG (6000) + Na2CO3 + DES was measured and correlated with merchuk equation. It is inferred from the data that molecular weight and complex molecular nature of HBD have a positive influence on physicochemical properties of DES and its Biphasic separation.
